<br>
We can't zone with our pets because of several things.<br>
<br>
1) Not sure, but I'm pretty sure each pet spell for us would require a buff icon appropriate for the type and level of the pet.<br>
<br>
2) Verant is under this misguided notion that they do not want us to be at full strength when we hit a zone. This KIND of makes sense, in essence, with the following understanding:<br>
<br>
  - If we have a buff icon on us indicating a Vocerate pet, the server (likely, currently) would make for us a NEW Vocerate pet, no equipment, no buffs, at full strength, at a new random level, just as if the pet were summoned anew. This would, in effect, 'reset' the pet, even if it were at 1hp on the other side of the zone. This is due in part to the fact that NPC pets are not 'saved' for crossing the zone barriers, and have to be recreated from scratch on the other side.<br>
<br>
  The only problem with this notion is that when we zone, Magicians certainly, we are definately not at our peak strength, even if we were undamaged previously. If we get into combat on the other side (say 1-2 mobs), we either run, try to channel through a pet, hope we can get enough distance to cast a pet, or die. Other classes (a la Paladins or Warriors or Monks or Rogues or Bards (melees)) are not so crippled in those circumstances.<br>
<br>
  And, to say that Mages get Invis to help them with travel, while that's nice and all, that doesn't stop Melees from getting Invis, and the proliferation of See Invis mobs makes relying on Invis for 'safe travels' flakey at best.<br>
<br>
I know we probably won't get Zoning pets until VI decides that they can save pet data across zones. They won't really consider that much of a priority, either, since there are more important things to spend their attention on. It would most certainly be NICE to have, even if we chose not to use it, but I don't anticipate ever seeing that feature. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Conjurer of the 59th Season<BR>
