<br>
The BL pet buff that determins the level of the pet costs about as much mana, and has about the same casting time as a Magician pet, Except at the earliest level.<br>
<br>
The beef people have with it being a C-Heal buff for the pet really isn't that big of a deal, Useing the BL pet buff that way is about the same as chaincasting an Elemental.<br>
<br>
Though unconfirmed by me, it is said that casting the pet buff resets all other buffs on the pet, so you basicaly have  a fresh pet when you buff it, with no other buffs.  The net advantage of the BL pet buff over chain casting is that there is no issue with timing the spell for when the pet dies.<br>
<br>
If, however, it does not wipe out other buffs in the process to use the BL pet buff as a heal, then that would be a bit more advantageous to the Beastlord. <p><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/atl/d/a/dastorys/Pictures/Necsig.jpg>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#333333>(7/17/02 6:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why can't our pet zone?</span><hr size=1> The Level Buff does, but does not, wipe the buffs on the BL Pet.<br>
<br>
What it does it set its Current and Max HP to a fixed number.<br>
<br>
If the pet has some sort of HP buff on it, the buff technically remains - the HP portion is just effectively eliminated. And, if it is a HP+AC, or HP+something else buff, the other effects apparently remain in full effect (until the normal expiriation of the buff).<br>
<br>
Example :<br>
<br>
A level 49 Beastlord get someone to cast Heroism on his pet.<br>
The pet has Base HP of 2400.<br>
Hero gives 360 HP (assuming it was cast by a 52 Cleric).<br>
<br>
The pet now has 2760 HP. Nothing unusual up to this point...<br>
<br>
Now, the BL recasts his pet buff to CH the pet...<br>
It is back to 2400 HP, and it still thinks it has Hero (with it's timer counting down).<br>
It still gains the 18 AC benefit for Hero.<br>
<br>
Assuming the pet lives long enough for Hero to expire, when that happens the pet still loses the 360 HP from Hero leaving it with 2040 Max HP............ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ussslippy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SSSlippy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#333333>(7/17/02 12:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why would you want it like that?</span><hr size=1> If you guys havnt noticed the beastlord pet and wizard familiar are BUFFS.  Buffs can be debuffed.  I would never want my pet dispelled.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujinnyhan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JinnyHan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(7/17/02 1:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why would you want it like that?</span><hr size=1> SSSlippy,<br>
